<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-547-409  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 547 409.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 19 1990 v7 n8 p21(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bankers Trust says its LAN will raise trading efficiency. (newdigital trading room designed around a DECnet-based local-areanetwork)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Panepinto, Joe.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Bankers Trust Co, in conjunction with DEC, designed a new digitaltrading room where traders at 250 VAXstation 3100-basedworkstations can simultaneously access and use real-time financialinformation provided by financial pricing services.andP;  The systemwas built around a DECnet-based local area network and usesDECtrade financial software.andP;  Traders are currently able to cutand paste information in different sectors of the screen toimprove the display, but the system does not yet support on-lineanalysis.andP;  Bankers Trust hopes to someday route pricinginformation into analytical software at each workstation.andO;Analytical capabilities would simplify on-the-spot purchasing andselling decisions.andP;  Integrating real-time market information andanalysis is possible with the new digital technology and enablesimproved portfolio management.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bankers Trust Co. (De Moines, Iowa) (Securities processing).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksFinancial ServicesReal-Time SystemsStock MarketOffice Automation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>